WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.360 --> 00:00:03.200
There are many sensors on your phone
that can be used to determine your

00:00:03.200 --> 00:00:06.000
location and
the context of what you're doing.

00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:08.440
To access these in a power friendly way,

00:00:08.440 --> 00:00:14.570
you can used the Fused Location Provider
and the Activity Recognition APIs.

00:00:14.570 --> 00:00:17.950
The Fused Location Provider
analyzes your GPS,

00:00:17.950 --> 00:00:21.920
your cellular connection And
your WiFi network.

00:00:21.920 --> 00:00:24.880
And it does this in order to
get the most accurate data.

00:00:24.880 --> 00:00:29.650
With this, you can also access
the user activity recognition service

00:00:29.650 --> 00:00:33.875
to determine, based on the movement of
your phone, if you're in a vehicle,

00:00:33.875 --> 00:00:36.970
if you're on a bicycle,

00:00:36.970 --> 00:00:41.530
if you're on foot, if you're standing
still, or even if you're tilting.

